article.description: All-American Kelly Mazzante scored 23 points to lead No. 13 Penn State past Michigan, 75-61, in Big 10 Conference action.
article.headline: Michigan can't overcome first-half deficit
article.linkText: Mazzante scores 23 to lead Penn State past Michigan
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Kelly Mazzante scored 23 points and
Tanisha Wright had 17 to lead Penn State (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) over Michigan 75-61 on Thursday night.

	   Jess Strom had 12 points and Jessica Brungo added 10 for Penn
State (22-6, 12-2 Big Ten), which used a 20-6 run late in the first
half to open an 11-point lead. The Nittany Lions led 37-26 at the
break.

	   Wright scored 10 of her points early in the second half to help
Penn State stretch its lead to as many as 24 points. Hazel Joseph
had 11 rebounds.

	   Jennifer Smith had 28 points for Michigan (11-13, 2-11), which
has lost eight straight.

	   Mazzante led the first-half run with 11 points in six minutes.
With the score tied at 24, she drove the lane and hit a shot over
three Michigan players, then converted on the ensuing free throw.

	   Michigan was in foul trouble early and Penn State hit 9-of-11
from the line in the first half.
